    "This issue is compounded by the uncertainty of whether subsequent chip designs adhere to the same specifications.",
    "On the other hand, dynamic and hybrid approaches offer more flexibility and potentially greater accuracy by incorporating real-time measurements and probabilistic models, yet they require sophisticated tools and expertise.",
    "The continuous evolution of real-time systems, especially in critical applications, necessitates further refinement of these techniques to ensure both functional accuracy and timely delivery of results [11].Conversely, our approach utilizes a black-box methodology, eliminating the need for detailed hardware and software modeling.",
